description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Cornwall Partnership NHS Foundation Trust (CFT) is excited to offer opportunities for Health Care Assistants within our inpatient community hospital settings. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;CFT provides a range of physical and mental health services to children and adults across Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly and we are seeking individuals with a passion for care who will relish the opportunity to showcase their caring approach and desire to help support our patients through their treatment and recovery pathway.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Via our internal Flexi Service we have opportunities in our inpatient settings where you will be supported, trained and empowered to utilise a range of skills, working alongside Registered Nurses and multi-disciplinary teams.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Along with our system wide health and care colleagues, we are working hard to blend resources and come together, in order to develop new and innovative ways to serve our communities. Therefore we need candidates who share our commitment to deliver the highest standards of care across our beautiful County.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you feel you have the drive and attributes we are seeking and share our passion, apply now and begin your new journey with us today.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Keri Podmore Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexi Team - cft.flexiteam@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01208 834664&lt;/p&gt;
